	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Especially in view of the potential druid rez (well, rez substitue, but it accomplishes the same thing), I support a similar ability for shamans, as I've said back on SKO.  In GoD groups, if your cleric gets eaten, it's a huge setback, and having a second rezzer can be a vital asset.  For this reason, 2 clerics are often preferred over cleric+druid or cleric+shammy.  <br />
<br />
Rez is basically a deal breaker when it comes to deciding between two classes for a group spot.  Leveling the playing field in that respect for the priest classes will help, even if it won't singlehandedly fix the class's issues.  <br />
<br />
SK's face the same problem when comparing to paladins.  The problem is that we have feign death, and giving us rez would mean we would go from behind pallys to ahead of them.  As such, you can't just give SK's rez without creating a similar problem in reverse.  We need a more creative solution to the problem - but something that would constitute equally desriable utility... <br />
<br />
Shamans don't face that problem - you, along with druids, could recieve a simple rez/rez substitute without creating a new balance problem.</p>
	
	
	
